title: Petition to trigger US House vote on release of Epstein files reaches required total – live
summary: Adelita Grijalva, the newest member of Congress from Arizona, has signed a petition aimed at compelling a House vote on legislation to release files related to Jeffrey Epstein. title: Bill to restrict late-term abortion defeated in South Australia after emotional debate
summary: A proposed amendment aimed to limit abortion access, permitting the procedure only when the mother's life is at stake, in cases of multiple pregnancies, or in instances of significant fetal abnormalities. The amendment sought to restrict previous broader abortion rights. Its implications could significantly impact reproductive health laws and women's rights.

title: Pressure grows on Starmer to sack chief of staff over briefing row
summary: There are increasing demands for Morgan McSweeney to resign following a controversial briefing operation aimed at discrediting Wes Streeting. Critics argue that the tactics used in the operation were unethical and damaging. The situation has sparked a significant backlash within political circles.

title: Anthropic announces $50bn plan for datacenter construction in US
summary: The AI startup responsible for the Claude chatbot is partnering with London-based Fluidstack to develop extensive new computing facilities. This collaboration aims to enhance their infrastructure to support advanced AI capabilities. The initiative reflects the growing demand for robust computing power in the AI sector.
